A 46-year-old boda boda operator charged with child pornography will know his fate next week. Tom Kidemi, a father of six, is accused of showing pornographic movies to children aged 12 and 13. ALSO READ:

Motorbike deaths increase by 17.7 per cent as riders lack licenses, safety gears He allegedly committed the offence at his home in Railways estate, Nakuru in March, last year. He was also charged with forcing children to engage in sexual acts and promoting child prostitution. He has denied the charges. The children who testified in court said Kidemi rewarded them with sugarcane after watching the movies and engaging in sex. Resident Magistrate Eunice Kelly yesterday said she would deliver judgement next week on Wednesday.